= Third Person Bio

Pierre Laforgue is a post-doctoral researcher at the University of Milan, working among the LAILA team led by professor Nicolò Cesa-Bianchi. His current research interests revolve around multitask online learning with applications to federated and privacy-preserving learning. Prior to this, he obtained his PhD from Télécom ParisTech, where he studied kernel methods and robust statistical learning under the supervision of professors Florence d'Alché-Buc and Stephan Clémençon.
